{"id":"1709.06156","submitter":"Yuan Chen","authors":"Yuan Chen, Soummya Kar, Jos\\'e M. F. Moura","title":"Resilient Distributed Estimation: Sensor Attacks","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.OC","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  This paper studies multi-agent distributed estimation under sensor attacks.\nIndividual agents make sensor measurements of an unknown parameter belonging to\na compact set, and, at every time step, a fraction of the agents' sensor\nmeasurements may fall under attack and take arbitrary values. We present the\nSaturated Innovation Update ($\\mathcal{SIU}$) algorithm for distributed\nestimation resilient to sensor attacks. Under the iterative $\\mathcal{SIU}$\nalgorithm, if less than one half of the agent sensors fall under attack, then,\nall of the agents' estimates converge at a polynomial rate (with respect to the\nnumber of iterations) to the true parameter. The resilience of $\\mathcal{SIU}$\nto sensor attacks does not depend on the topology of the inter-agent\ncommunication network, as long as it remains connected. We demonstrate the\nperformance of $\\mathcal{SIU}$ with numerical examples.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Sep 2017 20:31:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 20 Mar 2018 14:56:29 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 24 Jun 2018 19:43:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-26"}
