 mode is due to radio wave propagation across the quasi-transverse (QT)\nlayer. The abnormally high transition frequency (above 35 GHz) can be achieved\nreasonably low in the corona where the magnetic field value is high and\ntransverse to the line of sight. This places the microwave source below this QT\nlayer, i.e. very low in the corona.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 19 Sep 2017 04:49:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-27"}
