curate results for the\npurpose of asteroseismology. We apply our procedure in asteroseismic analyses\nof four \\textit{Kepler} stars and draw the same conclusions as in the solar\ncase: Correcting for structural deficiencies lowers the eigenfrequencies, this\ncorrection is slightly sensitive to the patching criteria, and the remaining\nfrequency discrepancy between models and observations is less\nfrequency-dependent. Our work shows the applicability and relevance of patching\nin asteroseismology.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 19 Sep 2017 10:20:36 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-20"}
